    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-07-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="35" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                <head>No. 35.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hale</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Jay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-07-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 10,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 226.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence in
                            regard to the Vienna Exposition of 1873, I have now to inclose herewith
                            a copy of an act of Congress of 10th June last, relating to the same,
                            and to inform you that Mr. Thomas B. Van Buren, of New York, has been
                            appointed by the President, by and with the advice and consent of the
                            Senate to represent the United States at said exposition.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES HALE,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
